description: Information on oil, gas, storage, solution salt, stratigraphic, and geothermal wells in New York State

Disclaimers.Limitations: Although every effort has been made to ensure the accuracy of information, errors may be reflected in the data supplied. The user must be aware of data conditions and bear responsibility for the appropriate use of the information with respect to possible errors, collection methodology, currency of data, and other conditions.

Dataset Summary.Organization: New York State Department of Environmental Conservation, Division of Mineral Resources
Dataset Summary.Dataset Owner: New York State Department of Environmental Conservation

columns.description: Unique 14-digit well identification number designed by the American Petroleum Institute (API) and referred to as the API number
columns.name: API Well Number

columns.description:
Three-digit code identifying the county where the surface of the well is
located; this code also appears as the third through fifth digits of the
API number. A list of the county codes and numbers appears in the attached Data Dictionary document.
(Note: The data does not display any preceding zeroes.)
columns.name: County Code

columns.description:
Five-digit code identifying the well; this code also appears as the sixth through tenth digits of the API number.

(Note: The data does not display any preceding zeroes.)
columns.name: API Hole Number

columns.description:
Two-digit code identifying any secondary wellbore, called a sidetrack, which is drilled out of and away from the original wellbore; this code also appears as the eleventh and twelfth digits of the API number.

(Note: The data does not display any preceding zeroes.)
columns.name: Sidetrack

columns.description:
Two-digit code identifying the number of operations, known as completions, which have occurred in a given wellbore to allow oil/gas to enter the wellbore; this code also appears as the thirteenth and fourteenth digits of the API number. 

(Note: The data does not display any preceding zeroes.)
columns.name: Completion

columns.description:
Financial security codes:

 TRUE – The well is subject to financial security requirements; 
FALSE – The well is not subject to financial security requirements 

Financial security is required for all wells drilled after June 5, 1973 to guarantee that funds will be available in the future for ultimate well plugging and surface restoration.
columns.name: Financial Security
